msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:97
msgid "Right: Use `git` to update sources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:99
msgid "Filenames:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:101
msgid "Wrong: ... in the filename [.filename]#/etc/rc.local#..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:103
msgid "Right: ... in [.filename]#/etc/rc.local#..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:105
msgid ""
"Manual page references (the second example uses `citerefentry` with the man:"
"csh[1] entity):."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:107
msgid "Wrong: See `man csh` for more information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:109
msgid "Right: See man:csh[1]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:111
msgid ""
"For more information about writing style, see http://www.bartleby.com/141/"
"[Elements of Style], by William Strunk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "Style Guide"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:116
msgid ""
"To keep the source for the documentation consistent when many different "
"people are editing it, please follow these style conventions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "Acronyms"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:121
msgid ""
"Acronyms should be defined the first time they appear in a document, as in: "
"\"Network Time Protocol (NTP)\". After the acronym has been defined, use the "
"acronym alone unless it makes more sense contextually to use the whole term. "
"Acronyms are usually defined only once per chapter or per document."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/fdp-primer/writing-style/chapter.adoc:123
msgid "All acronyms should be enclosed using the ` character."
msgstr ""

